<title>BELGIUM: Belgian bankruptcies up 10.9 pct in Q1 1997.</title>
<headline>Belgian bankruptcies up 10.9 pct in Q1 1997.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Company bankruptcies in Belgium rose by 10.9 percent to 2,147 in the first quarter of 1997 compared with the year-ago period, Belgian trade and company data group Infotrade said in a statement on Tuesday.</p>
<p>In March a total of 734 companies went bankrupt, up 8.7 percent from the year-ago month.</p>
<p>Infotrade said about 2,100 jobs had been lost in March as a result of the bankruptcies.</p>
